CONFIRMED genuine skip (#3) — needs the removed `emccanon` Python binding (direct canon emission from a handler).

oword.py's o<canonmove> emits motion directly from the handler via the emccanon
Python module: `emccanon.STRAIGHT_FEED(...)` and `emccanon.STRAIGHT_TRAVERSE(...)`.
gomc removed the embedded Python interpreter and the emccanon binding, and the C
interp_ext interp_ctx API deliberately exposes only a small canon surface
(canon_enqueue_set_spindle_speed / _feed_rate, tool select/change) — NOT motion
emission (STRAIGHT_FEED/STRAIGHT_TRAVERSE).

In gomc a remap/O-word produces motion through its `ngc=` body (plain G0/G1), not
by calling canon directly, so the "emit canon motion from inside a handler" path is
a genuine removal. (Re-adding it would mean extending interp_ctx with motion-emit
accessors — out of scope for a test re-expression.)
